    <div class="card">
      <h2>Speaking Requests</h2>
      <p>Nathan MacIntyre is available for speaking engagements related to rip current rescue, science, awareness, Great Lakes risk and prevention, lifeguarding expertise, and community education.</p>
      <p>The "Understanding Rip Currents" presentation is approximately 60 minutes and can be tailored for conferences, community events, municipal meetings, beach sessions, and public awareness initiatives.</p>
      <h3>Please include</h3>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>Event name and location.</li>
        <li>Preferred date, format, and audience size.</li>
        <li>Audience type and any local water safety concerns.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-muted">
  <div class="container grid grid-3">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>School Inquiries</h2>
      <p>Schools and educators interested in free water safety education are encouraged to get in touch.</p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>School name and location.</li>
        <li>Grade level or levels.</li>
        <li>Preferred format: classroom or beach-based.</li>
        <li>Preferred timing.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Municipalities & Local Governments</h2>
      <p>Municipal presentations focus on local risk factors, facility audits, standardized language, proactive beach management, and alignment across departments and partners.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Rescue Agencies & Responders</h2>
      <p>Sessions emphasize rip current science, how structures influence rescue risk, prevention messaging, and responder safety through public education.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

